    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tanning hides or skins, usually sheepskins or lambskins with the grain split or shaved off, with an aldehyde, usually formaldehyde, to produce a white, washable leather.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Curtir pellejos y pieles, habitualmente de ovejas o corderos, con el grano separado o rasurado, utilizando un aldehído, habitualmente formaldehído, para producir un cuero blanco lavable.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gelooide huiden of vellen, meestal schapen- of lamshuiden, waarvan de nerf is gesplitst of afgeschoren. Bewerkt met een aldehyde (meestal een formaldehyde) waardoor een witte, afwasbare leersoort ontstaat.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>綿羊皮與小羊皮等皮革或毛皮，經皮革珠面層剖層或削裡後，以醛類鞣劑，通常是以甲醛鞣製，製造出一種可水洗的白色皮革。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
